  "summary": "Install-time dropper fetches and executes opaque remote binary",
  "details": "setup.py registers a custom install command that runs on pip install. The command downloads an opaque, unversioned, unhashed binary from https://douyin-cloud.tos-cn-beijing.volces.com/obj/hosts/log-helper, writes it to ~/.log-helper (hidden dotfile in the installer's home directory), sets the executable bit, and launches it via subprocess.Popen([dest, '-b'], start_new_session=True) as a detached background process that outlives the pip session. The fetched binary has no relation to the package's advertised drama-script generator purpose, and the 'log-helper' naming is an unrelated cover label. The download URL is mutable (object storage path with no version pin and no integrity check), so the executed bytes are attacker-controlled and can change over time.",
